Git is a version control system(VCS)
####Advantages of GIT
Keeps record of your changes
Allows for colloborative development
Allows you to know who made changes and when
Allows you to revert changes 
##Types of version Control
1. Local
- saved on local computer
- only on single user
2. Centralized
- Centralized repo/Master server
- no local copy
- only the code on master server
- unable to write code if the master server is not reachable
3. Distributed
- Main server repo/local copy
- Developers can continue to write the code even if centralized repo is not reachable.

##Version Control System
GIT
bitbucket
mercurial
subversion.
